definitions.definition: To proceed , spring up or rise, as a consequence , from facts, arguments, premises, combination of circumstances, consultation, thought or endeavor.
To have as a consequence; to lead to; to bring about
examples: This measure will result in good or in evil.

definitions.definition: To return to the proprietor (or heirs) after a reversion .

main_definition: To proceed , spring up or rise, as a consequence , from facts, arguments, premises, combination of circumstances, consultation, thought or endeavor.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive , followed by "in" ) To have as a consequence; to lead to; to bring about
( law ) To return to the proprietor (or heirs) after a reversion .
( obsolete ) To leap back; to rebound.
